SIMPLE: frosting
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Frosting
<hw>Frost"ing</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A composition of
sugar and beaten egg, used to cover or ornament cake, pudding,
etc.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A lusterless finish of metal or glass; the process
of producing such a finish.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>the lightened color on part of an object, as of
hair, produced by treatment with bleach or other chemicals; as only part
of the object is thus treated, the final color of the object is
two-toned; also, the process of producing such a two-toned
effect.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Frostless</ent>⟦br⟧
